thread.title: Tennis Top Five Remains Intact

title: Tennis Top Five Remains Intact
text: Tennis Top Five Remains Intact Chap Carter & Mike Williams NCPrivateSchoolSports.com The NCISAA girls tennis will see, in the 1A, Wayne Country Day School vying for a third consecutive title. The WCDS Chargers have defeated all 1A opponents thus far and look solid to repeat as champions. In the 2A, St. David's School has won three consecutive titles and is a favorite to be in the final four. Charlotte Country Day School has two consecutive 3A crowns and is undefeated at this point with a 16-0 overall record. ... More ... To continue reading this article you must be a member.
